The paper deals with the geometric problem of transforming an arrangement of rectangles into an arrangement of squares while preserving its structure, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the combinatorial aspects of the problem, such as preserving the intersection graph, which could be classified under discrete mathematics (cs.DM) or graph theory (cs.GT). The paper presents a counterexample to a conjecture, which could be considered as a contribution to computational complexity (cs.CC) or computational theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper introduces a linear program for deciding the squarability of rectangle arrangements, which could be classified under data structures (cs.DS).
